1
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:05,857
A long time ago,

2
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:12,197
there lived a beautiful girl in a castle
located deep inside the forest.

3
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:19,245
She was always alone,
so she was lonely and bored.

4
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:24,250
So one day, she left the castle
to find herself a friend to play with.

5
00:01:27,545 --> 00:01:30,799
She offered them
all sorts of amazing gifts,

6
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:33,093
but nobody ever accepted her.

7
00:01:34,803 --> 00:01:37,555
Later on, she found out why.

8
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:41,392
A monster who brings along
the shadow of death.

9
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:43,645
That's what the people called her.

10
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:47,023
"She's a monster. A monster."

11
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:54,114
She was very angry
at every living soul in the world.

12
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:57,033
And she needed to take it out on someone.

13
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:34,696
Ever since she unexpectedly saved
the boy from dying,

14
00:02:35,947 --> 00:02:40,201
the scary shadow that always
followed her around suddenly disappeared.

15
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:46,875
And the boy always
followed her around instead.

16
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:51,588
He always went with her
whether it was day or night

17
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:54,591
and whether she was in the mountains
or a field.

18
00:02:57,760 --> 00:03:00,680
On a clear and sunny day,
the girl asked him this.

19
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:04,934
"Hey, will you always stay by my side?"

20
00:03:05,935 --> 00:03:08,396
"Of course. I will never run away."

21
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:11,649
"Even if I do this?"

22
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:29,417
The girl was all alone again,

23
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:32,754
and the shadow of death came back
and whispered this.

24
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:38,134
"No one can ever stay by your side

25
00:03:39,677 --> 00:03:43,139
because you're a monster.

26
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:48,394
Do not ever forget that.
Do you understand?"

27
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:51,940
Yes, Mother.

28
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:02,575
CHAPTER ONE
THE BOY WHO FED ON NIGHTMARES

29
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:14,712
This stop is Daun Vocational School.

30
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:17,757
The next stop is...

31
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:29,435
I mean, he threw a huge fit
in the middle of class.

32
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,687
My goodness.

33
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:32,438
No!

34
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,947
There's no use in trying to stop him.

35
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:43,157
And this isn't the first time.

36
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:44,575
Your expression...

37
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:46,995
What if there was a dangerous tool
next to him?

38
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:48,663
It would've led to an accident.

39
00:04:58,631 --> 00:05:01,426
I don't understand
why we need to walk on eggshells

40
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:03,386
-because of Sang-tae.
-Is he angry?

41
00:05:03,469 --> 00:05:04,721
Is he angry?

42
00:05:06,097 --> 00:05:08,182
Anyway, we need to think of safety,

43
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:10,310
-and he's too much for us to handle.
-Angry…

44
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:14,564
Just send him to a special needs school
or a local community center.

45
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:16,899
That will be best for everyone.

46
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:20,236
- Your expression shows your emotions
-Tell me what you think.

47
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:21,612
What do you think?

48
00:05:22,196 --> 00:05:24,657
Will you please say something?
My gosh, seriously.

49
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:41,883
He's angry.

50
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,052
THE BOY WHO FED ON NIGHTMARES

51
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:07,575
MOON SANG-TAE

52
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,344
Sang-tae.

53
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:29,555
Aren't you hungry?

54
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:37,355
What do you want to eat?

55
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:43,444
You weren't planning to stay
for long anyway.

56
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:49,450
I'll find you a better school
once we move. I promise.

57
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:57,417
-Are you that upset?
- Jjamppong.

58
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,502
-What?
- Tangsuyuk  with sauce on the side.

59
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:02,338
Let's go to Yangjagang, not Jageumseong.

60
00:07:04,173 --> 00:07:06,884
Okay, let's stuff ourselves with food
at Yangjagang.

61
00:07:06,968 --> 00:07:09,303
The food is really good there.
Do you remember?

62
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:12,807
When was the last time we went?

63
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:15,309
Don't worry. I'll buy.
I'm your big brother.

64
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:22,084
By any chance,
are you Author Ko Mun-yeong?

65
00:08:23,419 --> 00:08:25,463
-Yes.
-See? I told you.

66
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:29,217
My daughter is a big fan of yours.

67
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,052
I'm sorry to ask this,

68
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,805
but can we please get your autograph?

69
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:44,857
-Your name?
-Lee Seul-bi.

70
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:48,486
She's really beautiful in real life,
isn't she?

71
00:08:48,569 --> 00:08:52,281
Yes, she's like a princess
from a fairy tale.

72
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:02,583
-Why do you think so?
-Because you're pretty.

73
00:09:03,209 --> 00:09:06,420
My mom always calls me "princess"

74
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:07,838
because I'm pretty.

75
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:14,887
Ma'am, how about a photo?

76
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:16,556
My goodness, thank you.

77
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:17,890
Go stand next to her.

78
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:20,810
Come here.

79
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:28,609
You're not my fan, are you?

80
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:31,153
Pardon?

81
00:09:31,737 --> 00:09:35,408
In all my fairy tales,
the witch is always the one that's pretty.

82
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:40,079
Who told you
all princesses are kind and pretty?

83
00:09:40,871 --> 00:09:42,248
Did your mom tell you that?

84
00:09:42,331 --> 00:09:44,792
Princess, look over here.

85
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:49,088
If you really want to be that pretty,
I want you to say this.

86
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:51,465
-One.
-"Mom.

87
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:54,552
-I'm going to be...
-Two.

88
00:09:55,177 --> 00:09:58,306
a pretty witch."

89
00:09:58,889 --> 00:09:59,724
Three.

90
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:07,440
Princess.

91
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:10,443
-Oh, goodness.
-Princess!

92
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:14,030
My gosh.

93
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:18,618
My gosh. Mun-yeong.

94
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:24,248
Buongiorno,  Mun-yeong.

95
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:28,127
My gosh, what's with this chain?

96
00:10:30,546 --> 00:10:33,257
What made that little kid
cry her eyes out?

97
00:10:33,341 --> 00:10:36,218
I guess she was touched.
I corrected her misconception.

98
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:38,721
What in the world...

99
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:42,224
Good job.

100
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:46,354
It can be very dangerous
for a kid to be biased towards something.

101
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:48,105
But you helped her fix that?

102
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:51,609
You really are amazing, Mun-yeong.

103
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:53,736
Just a second.

104
00:10:56,364 --> 00:10:57,239
OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL

105
00:10:57,323 --> 00:10:59,492
I don't need a loan. I'm already rich.

106
00:11:02,953 --> 00:11:04,789
Okay, let's get going.

107
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:06,415
We have about two hours.

108
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,710
-So you have time to go to a beauty salon.
-Why would I go there?

109
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:13,464
You can't go looking like that.

110
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:17,551
You look like Francesca who's on her way

111
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:19,720
to a funeral for the Addams Family.

112
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:22,390
You can't go to a children's ward
looking like that.

113
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:26,394
You're going there to give kids hope,
not to scare them.

114
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:28,145
You'll be reading your books there.

115
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:30,981
-But you look--
-You said it's dangerous to be biased.

116
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:33,484
I think you're more dangerous.

117
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:36,946
Mun-yeong, please.

118
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:39,031
You should dress according to the TPO.

119
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:48,207
I'll tell them to come to you.

120
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:52,753
Do you know why I like this restaurant?

121
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:57,133
-Because the steak--
-No.

122
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,386
The knife here

123
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:02,555
is amazing.

124
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:07,518
-Look.
-Mun-yeong, you're bleeding.

125
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:10,730
How pretty.

126
00:12:12,773 --> 00:12:13,607
I want it.

127
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:19,655
Good gracious.

128
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,284
Ma'am.

129
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:26,495
Just a second.

130
00:12:58,319 --> 00:13:00,529
EMPLOYEE CARD CAREGIVER MOON GANG-TAE

131
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:04,074
Mr. Moon, come to the lounge quick.

132
00:13:09,705 --> 00:13:13,626
Gosh, that thief ate all my food.

133
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:15,753
It's as if she starved for days.

134
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:25,930
Ms. Myoung Ji-suk.

135
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:30,726
Honey.

136
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:40,861
I feel so empty.

137
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:44,198
Even so,
if you eat in such a hurry,

138
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:47,201
you'll get an upset stomach again.

139
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:49,745
So don't eat everything all at once.

140
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:53,624
Instead, it'd be great
if you could take your time

141
00:13:54,792 --> 00:13:56,585
to eat your food.

142
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:58,921
You told me you liked that I ate well.

143
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:02,633
You took it the wrong way.

144
00:14:02,716 --> 00:14:06,262
It's just that when you like someone,
you even like the way they eat.

145
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:11,600
Honey.

146
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:15,729
Then

147
00:14:17,439 --> 00:14:22,236
why did you cheat on me
with that skinny model?

148
00:15:16,665 --> 00:15:17,499
It's okay.

149
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:21,003
Don't smile at me.

150
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:23,505
It disgusts me.

151
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,471
-Put your arms up like this.
-Let me go!

152
00:15:30,554 --> 00:15:32,598
Then pull them down like this.

153
00:15:32,681 --> 00:15:34,767
-Stay still!
-I don't belong here!

154
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:37,519
Let me go! Let go of me!

155
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:39,563
I can't go in here! I can't!

156
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:43,067
Let go! I don't belong here!

157
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:44,610
-Is he a new patient?
-Let go!

158
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:47,321
He overdosed on alprazolam
with his daughter two days ago

159
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:48,530
and came through the ER.

160
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:51,075
He used to get treated
for his anxiety disorder.

161
00:15:51,158 --> 00:15:53,327
I think he tried
to commit suicide with her.

162
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:56,872
I think he wanted to kill his daughter
and then kill himself.

163
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:58,040
Where's Go-eun?

164
00:15:58,123 --> 00:16:01,377
Where is Go-eun? Where is my daughter?

165
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:04,213
Fortunately, she threw up
right after she took the drug.

166
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:07,967
And she's getting counseling for PTSD
at our child psychology department.

167
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:09,593
Go-eun.

168
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:11,887
What's on your mind?

169
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:15,182
Let me go!

170
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:17,977
He'll receive
a psychiatric assessment this afternoon.

171
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,645
So check his vitals every hour.

172
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:22,940
And double-check the restraining band
as you give him an IV fluid.

173
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:24,358
Okay.

174
00:16:25,192 --> 00:16:27,403
After the reading,
you'll answer questions.

175
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:30,864
Then you'll give out
your autographed storybooks to the kids.

176
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:34,576
And you'll be done once you take a photo
with the hospital staff for PR.

177
00:16:37,955 --> 00:16:41,417
I'm not sure if I'm a secretary
or the CEO of a publishing company.

178
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:44,086
I'm seriously starting to wonder.

179
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:46,672
I got hired as an art director.

180
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:50,426
But I had no idea
that I'd be working as your minion.

181
00:16:50,634 --> 00:16:53,137
You told me you'll do anything
during the interview.

182
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:57,641
Well, I didn't know
you'd make me do physical labor.

183
00:16:57,725 --> 00:17:00,185
I hired you
not knowing that you're not very smart.

184
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:02,396
What should I do? Should I just fire you?

185
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:03,814
No.

186
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,485
OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL

187
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,405
“OK Psychiatric Hospital”?

188
00:17:12,489 --> 00:17:13,991
Sir, do you get counseling?

189
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:16,285
You did the right thing.

190
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:19,413
Answer the phone.

191
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:27,171
-Hello?
-Put it on speaker.

192
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:32,384
Hello? Mr. Lee?

193
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:36,388
I'm Nam Ju-ri,
a nurse at OK Psychiatric Hospital.

194
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:37,973
Come this way.

195
00:17:38,348 --> 00:17:41,727
It's so hard to reach you.
You never text us back either.

196
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:44,813
Are you listening?

197
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:48,317
Oh, yes. I'm a bit busy--

198
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,651
I believe we told you

199
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:52,446
that we set a date
for Mr. Ko Dae-hwan's surgery.

200
00:17:55,574 --> 00:17:57,242
How long do we need to wait

201
00:17:58,577 --> 00:18:00,287
for the guardian's consent?

202
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,624
You can't keep avoiding
our calls like this.

203
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:07,086
That's the same thing
as killing the patient.

204
00:18:07,961 --> 00:18:09,046
Ko Dae-hwan.

205
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:12,216
He's dead to me.

206
00:18:13,383 --> 00:18:16,470
Why do you keep trying
to bring him back to life? Are you Jesus?

207
00:18:17,262 --> 00:18:18,555
-Excuse me.
- Ju-ri.

208
00:18:18,972 --> 00:18:22,476
If you're so desperate,
come and get the signature yourself.

209
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:46,500
What's wrong? What is it?

210
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,837
-What happened?
-She wants me to come and get it.

211
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:52,506
Is she out of her mind?

212
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,967
If she's not sane, she should come here.

213
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:56,176
Ms. Park.

214
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:58,971
Tell me about his medical history.

215
00:19:02,516 --> 00:19:05,686
-The patient in room 203 with dementia.
-Oh, Mr. Ko Dae-hwan?

216
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:10,232
He needs to get surgery
due to his glioblastoma relapse.

217
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:11,775
But his guardian doesn't care?

218
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:15,279
He has been with us
for the longest period of time.

219
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:18,782
But his guardian
never once visited or called

220
00:19:18,866 --> 00:19:21,034
which means he's being neglected.

221
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:25,205
So instead of just calling
his ungrateful guardian,

222
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:29,418
why don't you actually visit her in person
so that we can save the patient?

223
00:19:29,751 --> 00:19:30,752
What?

224
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:34,006
Is that really necessary?

225
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:37,384
You're going to do it, right?
I know you're a professional.

226
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:41,847
If you let me take the rest of the day
and tomorrow off,

227
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:44,683
-I'll go see her myself.
-Why two days?

228
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:47,227
Do you have a boyfriend in Seoul?

229
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:50,147
I guess you do.

230
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:52,983
Ju-ri, you have a boyfriend?

231
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:54,735
No.

232
00:19:55,152 --> 00:19:57,571
Well then, I'll be off soon.

233
00:20:00,532 --> 00:20:02,659
I bet she does have a boyfriend.

234
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,369
She's a traitor.

235
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:35,692
I don't think
your daughter will be able to come here.

236
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:47,788
No.

237
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:49,164
What's the matter?

238
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:52,417
No!

239
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:57,130
Die.

240
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:01,426
If she comes...

241
00:21:18,610 --> 00:21:21,196
FAIRY TALE READING
WITH AUTHOR KO MUN-YEONG

242
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:24,866
Gang-tae.

243
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:26,952
Yes?

244
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:30,497
I heard someone puked on you.

245
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:33,583
-She even slapped me.
-My gosh.

246
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:36,628
You should make sure
the day doesn't get worse.

247
00:21:37,045 --> 00:21:40,257
Kim Seung-cheol, who's in isolation,
will be sent to the police--

248
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:42,676
Yes, I heard. I'll take care of him.

249
00:21:43,510 --> 00:21:46,596
We had a team dinner last night,
and we made a bet.

250
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:48,307
"A bet"?

251
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:49,891
"Why does Moon Gang-tae

252
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:53,937
move from hospital to hospital every year
instead of settling down?"

253
00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:55,397
We tried to guess it.

254
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:57,482
Number one.

255
00:21:58,358 --> 00:22:01,111
You borrowed lots of money
and you're being chased after.

