00:40:48,779 --> 00:40:50,781
I see here that you've worked

510
00:40:51,282 --> 00:40:54,410
at so many different hospitals
in the past ten years.

511
00:40:54,827 --> 00:40:57,288
My gosh, 15 hospitals in total.

512
00:40:58,247 --> 00:41:01,750
And less than a year at all of them.
You've been here for ten months,

513
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,546
so you'll be quitting soon anyway.

514
00:41:05,629 --> 00:41:06,630
EMPLOYEE CARD

515
00:41:09,842 --> 00:41:11,135
Gang-tae.

516
00:41:14,138 --> 00:41:17,349
I'll say you worked here for a year
and give you the severance pay.

517
00:41:18,350 --> 00:41:19,768
Let's sort it out like that.

518
00:41:37,077 --> 00:41:38,579
Hey, it's me.

519
00:41:39,121 --> 00:41:42,291
Get me the number of the guy
who got hurt because of Mun-yeong.

520
00:41:43,417 --> 00:41:44,793
What do you think?

521
00:41:45,044 --> 00:41:48,339
I need to bribe him to silence him.
Come on. You know the drill.

522
00:42:22,873 --> 00:42:24,708
JAE-SU'S FRIED CHICKEN DELIVERY

523
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:34,385
I was delivering an order

524
00:42:34,468 --> 00:42:37,555
but saw a guy sitting like a sick chicken
and knew it was you.

525
00:42:45,396 --> 00:42:46,897
Hop on. I'll give you a ride.

526
00:42:48,649 --> 00:42:49,817
You freak.

527
00:42:52,736 --> 00:42:53,654
You're hurt again?

528
00:43:13,132 --> 00:43:14,508
Damn it.

529
00:43:15,718 --> 00:43:17,177
Is he ignoring my calls?

530
00:43:18,929 --> 00:43:22,182
If he bled, I'm sure he'll sue her.

531
00:43:23,684 --> 00:43:25,811
NURSE NAM JU-RI

532
00:43:29,982 --> 00:43:31,233
Hello, Ms. Nam.

533
00:43:32,151 --> 00:43:34,486
Oh, I see. You're already here?

534
00:43:35,738 --> 00:43:36,572
Right.

535
00:43:37,823 --> 00:43:39,491
The room number is...

536
00:43:42,077 --> 00:43:43,120
Just a moment.

537
00:43:50,753 --> 00:43:52,171
Did you order room service?

538
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:00,095
Where did he go?

539
00:44:51,522 --> 00:44:52,356
Thanks.

540
00:45:00,197 --> 00:45:02,491
Alberto, no. Don't do this to me.

541
00:45:02,574 --> 00:45:05,119
No, Alberto. Don't be like this.
Please, no!

542
00:45:05,828 --> 00:45:06,829
Don't do this to me!

543
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:08,455
-Shit.
-What's wrong?

544
00:45:08,539 --> 00:45:09,748
-Gosh!
-What's going on?

545
00:45:09,832 --> 00:45:12,042
Hang on, Alberto. Gosh!

546
00:45:14,044 --> 00:45:15,838
Alberto!

547
00:45:18,340 --> 00:45:19,842
Giddy-up!

548
00:45:19,925 --> 00:45:22,219
Alberto! Shit. Alberto, please...

549
00:45:23,387 --> 00:45:24,346
Don't die.

550
00:45:27,599 --> 00:45:28,434
Gang-tae!

551
00:45:29,935 --> 00:45:31,228
I'm really okay.

552
00:45:31,854 --> 00:45:34,732
Sang-tae must be waiting for you,
so just take a cab home!

553
00:45:35,983 --> 00:45:37,776
I won't say that you ditched me!

554
00:45:38,610 --> 00:45:39,695
I totally understand!

555
00:45:40,112 --> 00:45:43,407
Because that is
what a true loyal friend would do!

556
00:45:43,907 --> 00:45:45,576
Shut it and just keep on pulling.

557
00:45:49,246 --> 00:45:53,542
ANOTHER LONG DAY, RIGHT? CHEER UP!

558
00:45:53,625 --> 00:45:56,503
YOU WILL MEET YOUR SOUL MATE SOON.

559
00:46:16,732 --> 00:46:18,233
You've changed so much.

560
00:46:18,942 --> 00:46:21,945
I almost couldn't recognize you
because you don't look like a hick.

561
00:46:24,239 --> 00:46:27,284
Has it been almost 20 years
since I moved to a different school?

562
00:46:28,702 --> 00:46:29,536
Yes.

563
00:46:31,538 --> 00:46:34,374
We just need your signature here.

564
00:46:34,875 --> 00:46:37,836
The doctor must've already explained
everything over the phone.

565
00:46:38,378 --> 00:46:40,255
You should actually do it in person--

566
00:46:40,339 --> 00:46:42,716
Hey, you traveled for three hours

567
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:45,969
just to get my signature
on this stupid paperwork?

568
00:46:46,386 --> 00:46:49,431
Do you have a strong sense of duty?
Or are you a do-gooder?

569
00:46:54,353 --> 00:46:57,564
Our hospital is a psychiatric clinic,

570
00:46:58,232 --> 00:47:01,193
so we have to work with another hospital
to perform surgery.

571
00:47:01,652 --> 00:47:04,321
-In your father's case--
-I told you that he's dead.

572
00:47:06,448 --> 00:47:08,450
I'm an orphan. You know that.

573
00:47:10,869 --> 00:47:14,248
-But your mother is alive--
-I registered her death a long time ago.

574
00:47:15,874 --> 00:47:17,584
Do you know what's interesting?

575
00:47:21,922 --> 00:47:25,676
My dad's soul is dead,

576
00:47:26,343 --> 00:47:28,720
but he's physically alive like a zombie.

577
00:47:30,848 --> 00:47:32,099
As for my mom,

578
00:47:33,141 --> 00:47:35,269
she physically died many years ago.

579
00:47:37,020 --> 00:47:38,272
However,

580
00:47:42,025 --> 00:47:45,696
her soul is still alive.

581
00:47:53,954 --> 00:47:56,623
So between the two of them,
who's really dead?

582
00:47:58,250 --> 00:48:00,252
Tell me, nurse. Who's really dead?

583
00:48:02,254 --> 00:48:03,088
Your father...

584
00:48:04,631 --> 00:48:06,592
I mean, Mr. Ko Dae-hwan.

585
00:48:06,675 --> 00:48:09,678
He'll be in critical condition
without the surgery this time.

586
00:48:10,137 --> 00:48:11,346
His cognitive functions--

587
00:48:11,430 --> 00:48:14,016
Hey, others will think
that you're his daughter.

588
00:48:14,933 --> 00:48:17,519
Oh, why don't we do that?
You can be his daughter.

589
00:48:17,603 --> 00:48:19,021
I'll be your mom's daughter.

590
00:48:19,271 --> 00:48:22,941
I'll sign this consent form
if you agree to that. What do you say?

591
00:48:54,097 --> 00:48:55,849
Your mom is a good cook.

592
00:48:56,725 --> 00:48:59,937
Shall I come over for some food
like the good old days?

593
00:49:03,690 --> 00:49:05,651
I see that you still don't get my jokes.

594
00:49:07,903 --> 00:49:09,196
You're no fun.

595
00:49:12,866 --> 00:49:15,077
She pisses me off.

596
00:49:16,703 --> 00:49:18,038
She's insane.

597
00:49:18,121 --> 00:49:21,541
I can't believe she writes
children's book. That's bizarre.

598
00:49:21,875 --> 00:49:23,210
She's not "insane."

599
00:49:24,962 --> 00:49:26,421
She was just born that way.

600
00:49:26,505 --> 00:49:28,548
Gosh. Can you diagnose people at a glance

601
00:49:28,632 --> 00:49:31,259
now that you've worked
at mental hospitals for ten years?

602
00:49:32,094 --> 00:49:33,303
Stop overreacting.

603
00:49:33,387 --> 00:49:35,847
You fool, can you please learn
to overreact a little?

604
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:40,894
You got fired and got cut
because of those lunatics.

605
00:49:40,978 --> 00:49:43,522
I can't believe you just left
without causing a scene.

606
00:49:43,605 --> 00:49:44,773
Had I done that,

607
00:49:47,025 --> 00:49:48,360
it would've felt nice,

608
00:49:49,778 --> 00:49:52,072
-but I wouldn't get my severance pay.
-Well done.

609
00:49:52,864 --> 00:49:56,118
Your brother got expelled from school,
and you got fired from work.

610
00:49:56,201 --> 00:49:57,953
You guys are two peas in a pod.

611
00:49:58,578 --> 00:50:00,288
It was about time I quit anyway.

612
00:50:06,294 --> 00:50:07,671
It's this time of the year.

613
00:50:08,672 --> 00:50:10,340
When the night breeze feels warm.

614
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:12,634
I guess

615
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:16,888
butterflies will appear soon.

616
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:22,019
Right.

617
00:50:24,187 --> 00:50:27,357
How's Sang-tae? No signs yet?

618
00:50:29,067 --> 00:50:29,901
No, not yet.

619
00:50:31,069 --> 00:50:32,612
Then where should we go next?

620
00:50:35,615 --> 00:50:38,618
-Should we go to another country?
-Do you even have a passport?

621
00:50:38,702 --> 00:50:40,746
Sang-tae should learn English.

622
00:50:42,998 --> 00:50:43,832
Jae-su.

623
00:50:44,958 --> 00:50:46,543
Don't say anything to Sang-tae.

624
00:50:46,626 --> 00:50:50,380
Gosh, you only care about your brother.
I'm sick of this.

625
00:50:51,048 --> 00:50:52,507
I'm so jealous.

626
00:50:53,967 --> 00:50:54,968
You scared me.

627
00:50:57,596 --> 00:51:00,140
What's wrong?
Did she also hit you in the head?

628
00:51:02,642 --> 00:51:05,395
The autograph.
I forgot to get her autograph.

629
00:51:05,896 --> 00:51:08,565
-I promised him I'd get it.
-She must've hit you hard.

630
00:51:09,191 --> 00:51:10,025
What do I do?

631
00:51:11,109 --> 00:51:11,943
Oh, dear.

632
00:51:13,820 --> 00:51:15,822
AUTHOR KO MUN-YEONG'S AUTOGRAPH

633
00:51:26,500 --> 00:51:29,586
Gosh, her autograph
looks like a bunch of heroglyphs.

634
00:51:30,587 --> 00:51:33,256
Hieroglyphs, not "heroglyphs."

635
00:51:35,884 --> 00:51:37,469
Hurry up. Sang-tae is waiting.

636
00:51:46,311 --> 00:51:47,938
Done. Have a look.

637
00:51:49,106 --> 00:51:50,982
Look. It's very similar, isn't it?

638
00:51:59,157 --> 00:52:00,492
Nice job, Jae-su!

639
00:52:00,992 --> 00:52:03,120
Hey, quiet down.

640
00:52:06,081 --> 00:52:08,041
-Happy now?
-Yes.

641
00:52:09,167 --> 00:52:10,168
He'll be happy.

642
00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:15,549
Don't smile like that. It disgusts me.

643
00:52:17,968 --> 00:52:20,095
A patient said the same thing to me today.

644
00:52:21,596 --> 00:52:23,014
Is my smile that annoying?

645
00:52:24,224 --> 00:52:25,142
You don't know?

646
00:52:26,643 --> 00:52:27,894
You really don't know?

647
00:52:29,062 --> 00:52:31,314
-What?
-When you smile,

648
00:52:33,733 --> 00:52:35,402
you look like the Joker.

649
00:52:35,485 --> 00:52:38,530
With those sad eyes
and your lips pointing up like this.

650
00:52:40,448 --> 00:52:41,908
Look in the mirror. You'll see.

651
00:52:47,164 --> 00:52:47,998
Let's go.

652
00:52:56,173 --> 00:52:58,091
Sang-tae, I'm home.

653
00:53:05,974 --> 00:53:06,808
This...

654
00:53:09,769 --> 00:53:11,897
This is fake. It's fake.

655
00:53:11,980 --> 00:53:14,733
-No, it's real--
-This is fake.

656
00:53:15,066 --> 00:53:16,234
-That's…
-It's fake.

657
00:53:16,318 --> 00:53:19,029
-Sang-tae, wait.
-This is fake.

658
00:53:19,112 --> 00:53:22,782
-Goodness...
-This is fake.

659
00:53:22,866 --> 00:53:25,785
This is fake, fake, fake. It's all fake.

660
00:53:25,869 --> 00:53:27,871
You lied to me.

661
00:53:28,455 --> 00:53:31,541
-Sang-tae, I'm sorry.
-You lied to me.

662
00:53:32,751 --> 00:53:33,668
You lied to me?

663
00:53:33,752 --> 00:53:36,004
-Lying is bad.
-I was too busy today that...

664
00:53:36,087 --> 00:53:37,797
Lying is bad. You lied to me?

665
00:53:37,881 --> 00:53:40,091
Even little kids know
that it's wrong to lie.

666
00:53:40,175 --> 00:53:42,427
-Shall we go to the bookstore tomorrow?
-You lied?

667
00:53:42,510 --> 00:53:45,013
-Even a kid--
-Shall we get the dinosaur encyclopedia?

668
00:53:45,096 --> 00:53:47,307
-What?
-You always wanted that book.

669
00:53:49,184 --> 00:53:52,062
-Sang-tae?
-You lied?

670
00:53:52,771 --> 00:53:55,065
You lied? Why did you lie to me?

671
00:53:55,148 --> 00:53:59,402
-Lying is bad.
-Gosh, you poor thing.

672
00:54:01,821 --> 00:54:04,366
This is all Ko Mun-yeong's fault.

673
00:54:04,449 --> 00:54:07,369
I'm going to burn all these books!
What is this?

674
00:54:07,452 --> 00:54:09,412
-Why would a boy feed on nightmares?
-No!

675
00:54:09,496 --> 00:54:12,874
-No, don't.
-I'll burn all these books.

676
00:54:12,958 --> 00:54:14,542
-No!
-No? Why not?

677
00:54:14,626 --> 00:54:17,087
-It's mine. Don't do this.
-I'll burn them all.

678
00:54:17,170 --> 00:54:18,797
- Hello.
-Let go.

679
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:22,175
I am Lee Sang-in,
the CEO of SangSangESang Publishers,

680
00:54:22,259 --> 00:54:24,636
a children's book publisher.

681
00:54:27,305 --> 00:54:31,476
First of all,
I'd like to sincerely apologize

682
00:54:31,559 --> 00:54:35,021
for the unfortunate incident
between you and our author earlier today.

683
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:39,401
I'd like to speak with you

684
00:54:39,484 --> 00:54:41,945
if you can spare a moment
out of your busy schedule.

685
00:54:42,028 --> 00:54:43,905
It'd be greatly appreciated

686
00:54:43,989 --> 00:54:46,658
if you could stop by our office tomorrow.

687
00:54:47,701 --> 00:54:50,245
Please don't say no.

688
00:54:50,870 --> 00:54:53,707
I'd really like to meet you. Please.

689
00:55:02,757 --> 00:55:05,051
- Please!
-Why would you read children's books?

690
00:55:05,135 --> 00:55:07,721
You don't understand art.
Art is a beautiful thing.

691
00:55:07,804 --> 00:55:09,973
What do you mean I don't understand art?

692
00:55:10,056 --> 00:55:12,309
Naughty erotica books are what I call art.

693
00:55:12,392 --> 00:55:14,644
-This is--
-Go away. Just go home.

694
00:55:14,728 --> 00:55:16,855
-Just leave.
-Come on. I like you so much.

695
00:55:20,692 --> 00:55:23,236
Of course. I knew it. Let's see.

696
00:55:25,280 --> 00:55:26,114
Sure.

697
00:55:27,198 --> 00:55:29,909
"Sure"?
Gosh, that doesn't sound good.

698
00:55:29,993 --> 00:55:32,454
Around 6 p.m., at a Seoul hospital,
a man arranged

699
00:55:32,537 --> 00:55:35,707
- to be transferred to the police
-I have a bad feeling.

700
00:55:35,790 --> 00:55:38,710
after attempting to take his own life
as well as his daughter's

701
00:55:38,793 --> 00:55:41,796
was found dead in solitary confinement.

702
00:55:41,880 --> 00:55:43,923
The police are investigating his death.

703
00:55:44,382 --> 00:55:47,010
He caused a scene
at a book reading event

704
00:55:47,093 --> 00:55:49,346
which was held
for children in the hospital,

705
00:55:49,429 --> 00:55:53,016
but the security guards
were able to stop him immediately.

706
00:56:25,465 --> 00:56:28,760
He has such beautiful eyes.

707
00:56:41,106 --> 00:56:42,065
Do you know this?

708
00:56:42,941 --> 00:56:46,194
In this world,
there are people who deserve to die.

709
00:56:46,277 --> 00:56:50,407
But some thoughtful freaks
kill them for us in secret.

710
00:56:50,490 --> 00:56:53,952
That is why the clueless civilians
can sleep peacefully at night,

711
00:56:54,452 --> 00:56:55,954
completely unaware of it.

712
00:57:09,676 --> 00:57:11,845
What the…
I told you not to look down on me.

713
00:57:13,096 --> 00:57:14,806
Yes, I won't.

714
00:57:14,889 --> 00:57:17,725
-Stop him.
-Okay, go back to sleep.

715
00:57:37,412 --> 00:57:38,538
JAE-SU IS NOT ALLOWED!

716
00:58:03,021 --> 00:58:04,814
THE BOY WHO FED ON NIGHTMARES

717
00:58:34,135 --> 00:58:37,847
"The boy woke up
from another awful nightmare.

718
00:58:40,934 --> 00:58:43,353
Bad memories from the past
that he wanted to forget

719
00:58:43,895 --> 00:58:46,231
were replayed in his dreams every night

720
00:58:47,607 --> 00:58:49,234
and haunted him nonstop.

721
00:58:53,738 --> 00:58:56,741
Years went by,
and the boy became an adult.

722
00:58:57,951 --> 00:58:59,619
He no longer had nightmares.

723
00:59:00,161 --> 00:59:02,830
But for some strange reason,
he wasn't happy at all.

724
00:59:05,083 --> 00:59:07,293
One night,
a blood moon filled the night sky,

725
00:59:07,627 --> 00:59:09,420
and the witch finally showed up again

726
00:59:10,129 --> 00:59:13,132
to take what he had promised
in return for granting his wish.

727
00:59:14,217 --> 00:59:16,928
And he shouted at her
with so much resentment.

728
00:59:23,351 --> 00:59:25,395
'All my bad memories are gone. But why…

729
00:59:26,563 --> 00:59:28,356
Why can't I become happy?'

730
00:59:32,277 --> 00:59:35,530
Then the witch took his soul
as they had promised

731
00:59:35,905 --> 00:59:37,156
and told him this.

732
00:59:40,785 --> 00:59:42,453
'Hurtful, painful memories.

733
00:59:43,830 --> 00:59:45,206
Memories of deep regrets.

734
00:59:47,208 --> 00:59:49,335
Memories of hurting others and being hurt.

735
00:59:50,753 --> 00:59:52,589
Memories of being abandoned.

736
00:59:53,881 --> 00:59:58,052
Only those with such memories
buried in their hearts

737
00:59:58,928 --> 01:00:01,556
can become stronger, more passionate,

738
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:03,975
and emotionally flexible.

739
01:00:05,184 --> 01:00:07,937
And only those can attain happiness.'"

740
01:00:43,806 --> 01:00:45,099
Never forget today.

741
01:00:54,692 --> 01:00:55,818
You can't fall asleep?

742
01:00:57,528 --> 01:00:58,821
Where's my dad?

743
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:02,909
Everything will be okay. Don't worry.

744
01:01:04,410 --> 01:01:07,205
Will the police   take him?

745
01:01:08,998 --> 01:01:12,085
Will he be locked away
in a mental institution?

746
01:01:14,379 --> 01:01:17,882
Are you scared
that he'll show up again and harass you?

747
01:01:19,008 --> 01:01:20,551
That won't happen again.

748
01:01:22,512 --> 01:01:23,763
My dad...

749
01:01:26,057 --> 01:01:27,433
My dad is

750
01:01:28,643 --> 01:01:30,395
not a bad person.

751
01:01:31,229 --> 01:01:32,814
He's just not well.

752
01:01:33,481 --> 01:01:35,483
He's mentally ill.

753
01:01:37,652 --> 01:01:38,736
So please...

754
01:01:39,654 --> 01:01:42,031
Don't let the police take him.

755
01:01:43,199 --> 01:01:45,493
Please allow me to live with him.

756
01:01:47,203 --> 01:01:49,080
I want to live with my dad.

757
01:01:50,331 --> 01:01:52,083
I want to live with him.

758
01:01:53,710 --> 01:01:55,920
I miss my dad.

759
01:01:56,003 --> 01:01:58,423
- "So don't forget any of it.
-Dad...

760
01:01:58,506 --> 01:02:01,759
Remember it all and overcome it.
If you don't overcome it,

761
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:07,306
you'll always be a kid
whose soul never grows."

762
01:03:07,492 --> 01:03:09,285
What? Butterflies...

763
01:03:10,703 --> 01:03:12,079
No, those butterflies!

764
01:03:38,689 --> 01:03:41,776
-What? What's going on?
-Butterflies!

765
01:03:41,859 --> 01:03:43,736
-What's the matter?
-Butterflies...

766
01:03:43,820 --> 01:03:45,530
-Sang-tae.
-Butterflies...

767
01:03:45,613 --> 01:03:47,615
Gosh, those butterflies...

768
01:03:47,698 --> 01:03:49,784
Butterflies! Those butterflies!

769
01:03:50,409 --> 01:03:53,746
-Don't! I'm sorry!
-They're back. Those damn butterflies.

770
01:03:54,205 --> 01:03:55,957
Those butterflies!

771
01:03:56,040 --> 01:03:59,752
They said they'll kill me.
The butterflies will kill me!

772
01:03:59,836 --> 01:04:02,713
They're coming to kill me!

773
01:04:02,797 --> 01:04:05,341
-I have to run away.
-Sang-tae.

774
01:04:05,424 --> 01:04:08,010
I have to go. I must run away!

775
01:04:08,928 --> 01:04:10,179
Go away!

776
01:04:17,395 --> 01:04:18,604
Hey, Gang-tae!

777
01:04:18,688 --> 01:04:21,315
It's not even the peak moving season.
Why move out?

778
01:04:21,399 --> 01:04:23,025
Gosh, I can't believe this.

779
01:04:24,026 --> 01:04:24,861
Gang-tae!

780
01:04:26,237 --> 01:04:28,948
You still have months left on your lease.
Why do you...

781
01:04:29,031 --> 01:04:30,616
Gosh, you scared me.

782
01:04:30,700 --> 01:04:32,451
Mister, you slept here again?

783
01:04:32,535 --> 01:04:34,787
Then you need to chip in
for the water usage!

784
01:04:35,663 --> 01:04:37,248
Go bring the young man.

785
01:04:37,331 --> 01:04:40,251
We're friends. Why is he a young man
when you call me a mister?

786
01:04:40,334 --> 01:04:42,670
Cut it out. Where is he?

787
01:04:43,087 --> 01:04:44,463
I wonder too.

788
01:04:44,797 --> 01:04:47,341
Where on earth did he go so early?

789
01:05:07,612 --> 01:05:08,863
Mr. Moon Gang-tae?

790
01:05:12,283 --> 01:05:13,492
Hello.

791
01:05:13,993 --> 01:05:16,621
My boss is on his way back
from the print shop now.

792
01:05:16,704 --> 01:05:18,706
He said he'll be about ten minutes late.

793
01:05:47,109 --> 01:05:48,069
This way.

794
01:05:49,862 --> 01:05:52,114
Please wait here for a moment.

795
01:05:52,615 --> 01:05:53,449
Sure.

796
01:06:02,708 --> 01:06:06,504
THE HAND, THE MONKFISH

797
01:06:15,179 --> 01:06:16,681
AUTHOR KO MUN-YEONG

798
01:06:37,994 --> 01:06:41,038
Guys, she's here!
Clear your desks. Tidy up.

799
01:06:43,916 --> 01:06:44,917
Hurry.

800
01:06:56,345 --> 01:06:57,763
Who sits here?

801
01:06:59,181 --> 01:07:01,142
The accounting manager. Why do you ask?

802
01:07:02,309 --> 01:07:03,394
This is pretty.

803
01:07:03,477 --> 01:07:05,229
-I want it--
-Then you can have it.

804
01:07:05,855 --> 01:07:07,189
I was going to anyway.

805
01:07:14,238 --> 01:07:17,491
-Ms. Ko, what brings you by?
- Zombie Kid  is coming out today.

806
01:07:17,575 --> 01:07:19,493
-Where's Mr. Lee?
-Well...

807
01:08:02,578 --> 01:08:03,412
What a sight.

808
01:08:13,047 --> 01:08:14,715
You look dashing in regular clothes.

809
01:08:15,508 --> 01:08:18,260
Like an escort who's here to harass me
to pay off my tab.

810
01:08:21,138 --> 01:08:24,225
I thought you'd be different,
but I was obviously wrong.

811
01:08:24,809 --> 01:08:25,935
How much did he offer?

812
01:08:26,352 --> 01:08:29,146
If you can't talk politely,
at least try not to be so cryptic.

813
01:08:29,230 --> 01:08:31,440
And look at you talking to me so casually.

814
01:08:32,817 --> 01:08:34,151
I practically stabbed you.

815
01:08:37,446 --> 01:08:39,782
-What about it?
-How much did Mr. Lee offer you

816
01:08:40,950 --> 01:08:42,201
to compensate you for that

817
01:08:42,535 --> 01:08:45,579
as well as to make sure
you won't tell anyone about it?

818
01:08:49,041 --> 01:08:50,668
I guess this has always worked.

819
01:08:50,751 --> 01:08:52,336
Verbal consolation is useless.

820
01:08:52,419 --> 01:08:53,504
Money is the best.

821
01:08:55,381 --> 01:08:56,382
Not to me.

822
01:08:57,216 --> 01:08:59,218
Then what do you want? Sex?

823
01:09:00,553 --> 01:09:01,971
Is it worth more than money?

824
01:09:05,391 --> 01:09:06,600
Then why are you here?

825
01:09:06,684 --> 01:09:09,812
If not for money or sex,
what are you here for?

826
01:09:14,608 --> 01:09:15,568
I was hoping

827
01:09:19,780 --> 01:09:21,115
I could see you

828
01:09:22,575 --> 01:09:23,409
again.

829
01:09:27,371 --> 01:09:28,205
Your eyes.

830
01:09:30,249 --> 01:09:31,876
I wanted to see them again.

831
01:09:35,754 --> 01:09:36,589
My eyes?

832
01:09:38,132 --> 01:09:38,966
Your eyes

833
01:09:41,927 --> 01:09:44,054
remind me of someone I used to know.

834
01:09:48,058 --> 01:09:49,059
Who is that person?

835
01:09:51,854 --> 01:09:53,355
Someone who's messed up

836
01:09:56,942 --> 01:09:58,944
and has no conscience.

837
01:09:59,987 --> 01:10:00,988
A woman

838
01:10:02,948 --> 01:10:04,200
whose eyes

839
01:10:06,118 --> 01:10:07,203
utterly lacked warmth.

840
01:10:14,668 --> 01:10:15,544
That woman...

841
01:10:20,216 --> 01:10:21,342
Were you afraid of her?

842
01:10:26,222 --> 01:10:27,097
No, the opposite.

843
01:10:45,074 --> 01:10:47,826
I liked her.

844
01:12:00,441 --> 01:12:01,650
Are you that excited?

845
01:12:01,734 --> 01:12:04,903
"Dear Sang-tae!
Please come to my book launch party."

846
01:12:04,987 --> 01:12:07,614
It's boring to say
that we're destined for each other.

847
01:12:07,698 --> 01:12:09,074
I thought I was on the run…

848
01:12:09,700 --> 01:12:10,701
Don't touch my hair!

849
01:12:10,784 --> 01:12:12,202
because of my brother.

850
01:12:13,078 --> 01:12:14,288
Coward.

851
01:12:14,371 --> 01:12:16,582
Where is Ko Mun-yeong?

852
01:12:16,999 --> 01:12:19,585
You won't end up well
if you get involved with her.

853
01:12:20,878 --> 01:12:23,297
-Don't go.
-I want you to be my safety pin.

854
01:12:23,630 --> 01:12:27,217
Keep me under control
so that I won't explode.

855
01:12:36,268 --> 01:12:40,814
The boy woke up
from another awful nightmare.

856
01:12:41,607 --> 01:12:44,485
Bad memories from the past
that he wanted to forget

857
01:12:44,568 --> 01:12:47,863
were replayed in his dreams every night

858
01:12:47,946 --> 01:12:50,574
and haunted him nonstop.

859
01:12:51,325 --> 01:12:53,869
The boy was terrified of falling asleep.

860
01:12:53,952 --> 01:12:57,039
So one day,
he went to the witch and begged.

861
01:12:57,998 --> 01:13:01,001
"Please get rid of all my bad memories

862
01:13:01,335 --> 01:13:04,213
so that I won't ever have
a nightmare again.

863
01:13:05,255 --> 01:13:08,008
Then I will do everything you ask."

864
01:13:09,635 --> 01:13:12,262
Years went by,
and the boy became an adult.

865
01:13:12,596 --> 01:13:14,848
He no longer had nightmares.

866
01:13:15,432 --> 01:13:19,228
But for some strange reason,
he wasn't happy at all.

867
01:13:21,063 --> 01:13:23,399
One night,
a blood moon filled the night sky,

868
01:13:23,482 --> 01:13:25,317
and the witch finally showed up again

869
01:13:25,401 --> 01:13:28,821
to take what he had promised
in return for granting his wish.

870
01:13:29,154 --> 01:13:32,282
And he shouted at her
with so much resentment.

871
01:13:33,117 --> 01:13:35,911
"All my bad memories are gone. But why...

872
01:13:36,787 --> 01:13:38,705
Why can't I become happy?"

873
01:13:39,540 --> 01:13:43,085
Then the witch took his soul,
as they had promised,

874
01:13:43,168 --> 01:13:44,586
and told him this.

875
01:13:45,129 --> 01:13:47,172
"Hurtful, painful memories.

876
01:13:47,673 --> 01:13:49,466
Memories of deep regrets.

877
01:13:50,092 --> 01:13:53,137
Memories of hurting others and being hurt.

878
01:13:53,762 --> 01:13:55,639
Memories of being abandoned.

879
01:13:56,223 --> 01:14:00,185
Only those with such memories
buried in their hearts

880
01:14:00,269 --> 01:14:02,813
can become stronger, more passionate,

881
01:14:03,355 --> 01:14:06,066
and emotionally flexible.

882
01:14:06,942 --> 01:14:10,362
And only those can attain happiness.

883
01:14:11,196 --> 01:14:14,700
So don't forget any of it.
Remember it all and overcome it.

884
01:14:15,159 --> 01:14:16,535
If you don't overcome it,

885
01:14:17,661 --> 01:14:21,373
you'll always be a kid
whose soul never grows."

886
01:14:24,001 --> 01:14:25,961
Subtitle translation by Liya Choi
